<TITLE> 1 killed in Madaripur road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Madaripur, Nov 03 (bdnews24.com)  One died and three others were injured in a road accident on Tuesday in Madaripur. It happened when a fully loaded Nosimon (human hauler) slid into a ditch, Shibchar police chief MA Jalil said. "A Nosimon lost control and fell into a roadside ditch while it was running across Charvadrashon around 10am. A passenger named Rakib, 10, died on the spot," Jalil told bdnews24.com. Abdur Rahim, the driver, was admitted to Dhaka Medical College and Hospital with serious injury, he added. Kanchan Bepari and Nannu Bepari were also injured and were taken to Shibchar Upjilla medical centre. bd
